{{see|force}}
==English==

===Etymology===
Coined by George Lucas for the film ''Star Wars''

===Noun phrase===
{{Wikipedia|Force (Star Wars)}}
'''The Force'''
# A mystical power which is the object of the [[Jedi]] and [[Sith]] [[religion]]s.
#: ''Use The Force, Luke''

===Quotations===
*'''1977:''' ''[[w:Star Wars Episode IV: A New Hope|Star Wars Episode IV: A New Hope]]''
**[[Obi-Wan Kenobi]] (postmortem): "Use the '''Force''', Luke."
*'''2005:''' ''[[w:Star Wars Episode III: Revenge of the Sith|Star Wars Episode III: Revenge of the Sith]]''
**Palpatine: "Good. Good. The '''Force''' is strong with you. A powerful Sith you will become. Henceforth, you shall be known as Darth...Vader."

